function rexLocalSampleAnswer(question,evidence,focus,intent){var topic=focus||"the role",proof=evidence&&evidence.length?" In your case, I would connect this to: "+evidence[0]:"";if(intent==="data"){return "Sample answer:\nI would start by clarifying the decision the data needed to support, then check the quality of the source information before building the analysis. I would look for patterns, exceptions, and risks, summarise the findings clearly, and turn them into practical recommendations. This shows that I do not just produce reports; I use analysis to help people make better decisions."+proof;}if(intent==="healthcare"){return "Sample answer:\nI would approach this by keeping the person receiving care at the centre of the situation. I would listen carefully, check the facts, follow the correct process, communicate with the relevant team members, and document what happened accurately. That approach protects safety, dignity, and continuity of care while showing that I can stay calm and professional."+proof;}if(intent==="motivation"){return "Sample answer:\nI am interested in this role because it matches the kind of work where I can contribute quickly: understanding what is needed, organising the task properly, communicating clearly, and delivering to a reliable standard. What attracts me most is the chance to use my experience in "+topic+" in a role where accuracy, judgement, and service matter."+proof;}return "Sample answer:\nI would approach "+topic+" by first clarifying the outcome needed, then choosing the most relevant evidence from my experience. In a previous situation, I had to organise the work, communicate with the right people, and maintain quality while dealing with competing priorities. I focused on the practical actions I could control, kept people updated, and followed through until the work was completed. The result was a clearer process, stronger confidence in the outcome, and a better standard of delivery."+proof;}
